@startuml

actor User
participant "Nginx\nReverse Proxy" as Nginx
participant "Backend\nServer" as Backend
participant "Socket.IO\nServer" as SocketIO
database "MySQL" as MySQL
database "InfluxDB" as InfluxDB
database "Redis" as Redis
participant "Docker\nSandbox" as Sandbox
cloud "AWS EC2" as EC2
cloud "AWS S3" as S3
cloud "AWS CloudFront" as CDN
cloud "AWS CloudWatch" as CW

User -> Nginx: HTTP Request
Nginx -> Backend: Route request

Backend -> MySQL: Query data
Backend -> InfluxDB: Store time-series data
Backend -> Redis: Cache data

Backend -> SocketIO: Emit real-time events
SocketIO -> User: Send real-time updates

Backend -> Sandbox: Execute code
Sandbox --> Backend: Return execution results

Backend -> S3: Store files
S3 -> CDN: Serve content

Backend -> CW: Log events

Backend --> Nginx: Send response
Nginx --> User: Deliver response

note right of EC2
  EC2 instance hosts:
  - Nginx
  - Backend Server
  - Socket.IO Server
  - MySQL
  - InfluxDB
  - Redis
  - Docker Sandbox
end note

@enduml